M||tx|---
M||titl|Use toSorted() Instead of sort() for Immutability
M||impa|md-hi
M||impa|prevents mutation bugs in rc state
M||tags|javascript, arrays, immutability, rc, state, mutation
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|`.sort()` mutates the array in place, which can cause bugs w/ rc state and props. Use `.toSorted()` to cr a new sorted array w/o mutation.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |func|{ us: us[] }) {
M|Use |tx|// Mutates the us prop array!
M|Use |tx|const sorted = useMemo(
M|Use |tx|() => us.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
M|Use |tx|[us]
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|return <div>{sorted.map(renderUser)}</div>
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |func|{ us: us[] }) {
M|Use |tx|// Creates new sorted array, original unchanged
M|Use |tx|const sorted = useMemo(
M|Use |tx|() => us.toSorted((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name)),
M|Use |tx|[us]
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|return <div>{sorted.map(renderUser)}</div>
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Wh|**
M|Use |tx|1. Props/state mutations break rc's immutability md - rc expects props and state to be treated as read-only
M|Use |tx|2. Causes stale closure bugs - Mutating arrays inside closures (callbacks, effects) can lead to unexpected behavior
M|Use |**Br|**
M|Use |`.to|
M|Use |tx|```ts
M|Use |tx|// Fallback for older browsers
M|Use |tx|const sorted = [...items].sort((a, b) => a.value - b.value)
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Ot|**
M|Use |it|`.toSorted()` - immutable sort
M|Use |it|`.toReversed()` - immutable reverse
M|Use |it|`.toSpliced()` - immutable splice
M|Use |it|`.w/()` - immutable element replacement